== 8...a6 ==
Black protects the b-pawn so they can play 9...c5 without blundering a pawn.

Foreseeing this plan, White should play actively and take over the center with '''[[/9. e4/]]''', preparing to open up the center with either 10. d5 or 10. e5 and opening up the dark-squared bishop.

Less provocative setups have been tried as well. At the amateur level '''[[/9. O-O/]]''' is very popular, but this poses no problems for players with the black pieces at all, since they score quite well in this line.

Another move that is played often is '''[[/9. a4/]]'''. White does better than after 9. O-O, but has lost quite a bit of initiative.

